name: Rainbow Cookies Composition 1
description: Dedicated to my grandfather, my Opa, who knew hunger. Together with my Oma, he gave us many treats when I was a child, so that we would not experience the same. Rainbow cookies are an NYC treat that are so common in Jewish bakeries that only as an adult did I learn they are actually Italian. They have 3 thick cakey layers with jam between each one. Cherry cordials were a favorite of his.
